<Base title="About — Pangaea">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    Pangaea is a weekly catalog by <a href="https://adamtpang.substack.com">Adam Pang</a>. Each
    issue — a <em>rift</em> — bundles three things I'd want a friend to know about that week:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>One <strong>app</strong> — software worth your attention.</li>
    <li>One <strong>essay</strong> — something I read and can't stop thinking about.</li>
    <li>One <strong>song</strong> — sent for the obvious reason.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Sometimes a picture, a video, a quote. Pangaea was the supercontinent before everything broke
    apart. Music, philosophy, technology — these don't feel separate to me, and this is the place I
    keep them on the same map.
  </p>

  <h2>Why "rift"</h2>
  <p>
    A rift is where the ground opens. Continents pull apart and something new appears in the seam.
    Each issue is a small opening into the things I'm paying attention to.
  </p>

  <h2>Cadence</h2>
  <p>
    Weekly, mostly. The newsletter version lives at{' '}
    <a href="https://adamtpang.substack.com">adamtpang.substack.com</a> — same content, in your
    inbox.
  </p>

  <h2>Lineage</h2>
  <p>
    A nod to the <em>Whole Earth Catalog</em> — small, useful, hand-picked, personal. With debt
    also to <a href="https://sive.rs">Derek Sivers</a>, <a href="https://waitbutwhy.com">Tim Urban</a>,
    and the long tradition of writers who own their words at their own URLs.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <p class="meta">
    Find me elsewhere: <a href="https://adamtpang.substack.com">Substack</a> ·{' '}
    <a href="https://github.com/adamtpang">GitHub</a>
  </p>
</Base>
